{"id":14881054,"mediaExerciseId":"e3125d28-379a-4f64-937c-a141db29fe10","exerciseName":"5","chapterName":"7","chapterTitle":"Interest Rates and Bond Valuation","groupId":612313,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":233,"solutions":[{"id":5993995,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this task, **we should calculate the coupon value of the Gabriele Enterprises bond.**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Coupon rates are determined by the entity that issues a bond. The coupon value will be the same for every future payment. So it is a fixed amount.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"The exercise says that the bond is selling at \\$948. That is the bond price. To calculate the coupon rate, we can use the formula for the bond's price.\n\n$$\\text{price of the bond}=\\text{C}\\times\\dfrac{1-\\left(1+\\text{YTM}\\right)^\\text{-n}}{\\text{YTM}}+\\dfrac{\\text{F}}{\\left(1+\\text{YTM}\\right)^\\text{n}}$$\n\n$C$ - what we have to find (coupon)\n\n$YTM$ - bond yield\n\n$F$ - par value\n\n$n$ - period\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":62,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/7e5b992bd2717aec62f649620c949184/a87033cd7fbcea102f3edc8e81091a33/lateximg_large.png","width":1019},"regular":{"height":31,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/7e5b992bd2717aec62f649620c949184/a87033cd7fbcea102f3edc8e81091a33/lateximg.png","width":510}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's insert all the data in the previous formula and then calculate the coupon.\n\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n\\$948&=\\text{C}\\times\\dfrac{1-\\left(1+0.051\\right)^{-8}}{0.051}+\\dfrac{\\$1,000}{\\left(1+0.051\\right)^8}\\\\\n\\\\\n\\$948&=\\text{C}\\times\\dfrac{1-0.671}{0.051}+\\$671.704\n\\end{aligned}\n$$","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/7e5b992bd2717aec62f649620c949184/59a6514dfb0376f272f20bd7fd822ea7/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/7e5b992bd2717aec62f649620c949184/59a6514dfb0376f272f20bd7fd822ea7/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"Now, we can simplify the previous expression and find the value of the coupon.\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{C}\\times6.437&=\\$948-\\$671.704\\\\[15pt]\n&=\\dfrac{\\$948-\\$671.704}{6.437}\\\\[15pt]\n&=\\boxed{\\$42.92}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\n\\$42.92 is the amount of the coupon. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":372,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/7e5b992bd2717aec62f649620c949184/5bd780770120c3437ef94d4d168a6a88/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":188,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/7e5b992bd2717aec62f649620c949184/5bd780770120c3437ef94d4d168a6a88/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"To get the coupon rate, we have to divide \\$42.92 by face value to get the rate.\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{coupon rate}&=\\dfrac{\\$42.92}{\\$1,000}\\times100\\\\[15pt]\n&=\\boxed{4.292\\%}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\n**The coupon rate is 4.292\\%.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":269,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/7e5b992bd2717aec62f649620c949184/cd1d8208cfd23d3ce22621e06593f178/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":136,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/7e5b992bd2717aec62f649620c949184/cd1d8208cfd23d3ce22621e06593f178/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"94387873-24f2-46af-bf51-4dc0b1872529","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":6}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881055,"exerciseName":"6","page":233,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"950c2961-96ce-463d-a7a5-57818771924c","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-questions-and-problems-6-950c2961-96ce-463d-a7a5-57818771924c"},{"id":14881056,"exerciseName":"7","page":233,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"2e053a52-210d-4a10-8229-2a699d541d43","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-questions-and-problems-7-2e053a52-210d-4a10-8229-2a699d541d43"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881053,"exerciseName":"4","page":233,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"ff990349-44be-481c-b92a-0087b3ac2177","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-questions-and-problems-4-ff990349-44be-481c-b92a-0087b3ac2177"},{"id":14881052,"exerciseName":"3","page":233,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"387d9a43-c419-4